news.title: Vadodara: Shops without fire safety face heat
news.para: On Monday, four commercial complexes including the Sitaram Complex and Kunj Plaza in Chhani, VIP View Complex in Karelibaug as well as Maruti Complex in Nizampura were sealed.

news.title: Noida: Air turns 'very poor', but demolition waste dumping goes unchecked here
news.para: Though the Commission for Air Quality Management (CAQM) implemented stage 2 of the Graded Response Action Plan (GRAP) in DelhiNCR and adjoining areas on Saturday, the same is not visible on the ground.

news.title: MCD issues 24 challans for dumping of C&D waste in Delhi
news.para: MCD has formed 511 surveillance teams, comprising 1,064 officials, to check open burning, illegal construction, demolition waste dumping and dust on roads. It has also stationed 35 anti-smog guns at high rise buildings and landfills.

news.title: Nashik civic body sends notices to 2.4 lakh property tax defaulters
news.para: The NMC has directed the defaulters to clear their tax dues within 15 days, failing which, the civic body will start the process of issuing warrants.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government hikes payout for phase-2 of Noida airport by Rs 880 crore
news.para: Officials said 70% of acquisition of 1,181 hectares of land across six villages in Jewar — Ranhera, Kureb, Karauli Bangar, Dayanatpur, Beerampur and Mudharah — has been completed and compensation of Rs 2,800 crore distributed to farmers till now.

news.title: Density a pivotal issue: Chief architect on Chandigarh master plan
news.para: Surinder Bahga, a city-based architect, pointed out lack of a proper documentation process to identify heritage buildings, uncertainties over preservation methods and responsible parties, and the need for a clear administrative approach.

news.title: Daily property registrations in Maharashtra witness uptick in past week
news.para: This was the trend in September too, a registration official said on Monday. Data showed that from October 16, the registrations were over 11,000 a day and October 20 witnessed the highest daily log (13,569) for the month.

news.title: The slow and steady revival of malls in Gujarat
news.para: According to mall owners, rising appetite for luxury, more awareness and increasing disposable incomes are among key reasons for retail trade to grow overall, and as a result, malls as organized retail spaces are doing good business.

news.title: Plans to scan eight crore pages of real estate documents in Maharashtra
news.para: The registration department fears that photo films from the last 58 years are prone to damage and they should be digitised. Similar documents post-2002 are in a digital format.

news.title: Real estate developers in Gujarat issued notices for royalty dues
news.para: However, developers are contesting this move, claiming that it’s not practical, particularly for projects completed around five years ago, as calculating the volume of ordinary clay, murrum, and minerals excavated has become a challenging task.

news.title: Consumer panel orders Antriksh NRI City's builder to pay 6% interest on refund amount
news.para: The commission was not satisfied with the argument of the developer that it was unable to pay the refund due to Covid-19. Malik had paid a partial consideration amount of Rs 6.4 lakh to the developer to purchase a plot worth Rs 34 lakh.

news.title: Lenders to Gayatri Projects get lone resolution bid offering 10% recovery
news.para: The bankers had received two expressions of interest (EOIs) earlier this year but the other joint bid from two individuals did not result in a serious offer, people familiar with the process said.

news.title: M3M promoter files pre-emptive bail plea in graft case
news.para: Bansal and the Parmars are in the Ambala jail in two separate cases that the enforcement directorate had registered. Bansal was arrested in the 2021 money laundering case that involved Ireo realty group managing direcotr Lalit Goyal.

news.title: Qualcomm rents 600,000 sq ft office space in Bengaluru to expand operations
news.para: The new office will come up in Bagmane Capital-Angkor in Bengaluru, a major hub for technology firms. The space will be taken up in two phases by Qualcomm. "Qualcomm will occupy ground plus 12 floors in the upcoming facility for a tenure of 108 months," mentioned the document.

news.title: Signatureglobal (India) acquires 25.75 acres land in Gurugram
news.para: According to Signatureglobal (India) red hearing prospectus, it is in advance discussions with landowner to enter in to a joint development agreement for 16.12 acres land and has entered into a term sheet in the same vicinity.

news.title: Aurum PropTech's net loss widens to Rs 23.89 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Aurum PropTech's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 57.53 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 86.54 per cent from Rs 30.84 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: MQDC India invests over Rs 10 crore to develop 42,000 sq ft co-working space in Gurugram
news.para: Spread over 42,000 sq ft, this co-working space offers a seating capacity of over 450. MQDC India expects 20-30 per cent occupancy in next 1-2 months for this center.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance's net profit increases by 45.83% in Q2 FY24
news.para: PNB Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,779.40 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 5.70 per cent from Rs 1,683.43 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
